The body of the late Nyeri Governor Nderitu Gachagua has left Lee Funeral Home and the convoy is heading to his home in Hiriga Village, Mathira West where he will be laid to rest. The late Governor died on February 24 in a London Hospital where he was undergoing treatment for pancreatic cancer that he has been ailing for a long time. The funeral service is scheduled to begin at 11 am at his home. President Uhuru Kenyatta and all Governors are expected to attend the funeral at his home in Nyeri. ALSO READ: Body of Governor Gachagua arrives from London